01:55.323 --> 01:57.575
[Rupert Holmes' "Escape" playing]

01:59.077 --> 02:00.995
♪ And gettin' caught in the rain ♪

02:02.664 --> 02:04.374
I've never felt more alive--

02:05.959 --> 02:08.253
♪ If you have half a brain ♪

02:09.295 --> 02:11.631
--more honest than I do right now.

02:12.715 --> 02:14.884
♪ In the dunes on the cape ♪

02:16.094 --> 02:18.847
♪ I'm the love that you've looked for ♪

02:19.889 --> 02:21.391
I've never felt this free...

02:23.017 --> 02:24.519
to be who I am.

02:25.145 --> 02:26.271
And it's because of you.

02:35.155 --> 02:37.991
Uh, honey, have you seen my, uh...?

02:40.535 --> 02:41.369
What?

02:42.620 --> 02:44.247
My-- What do you call them?

02:44.831 --> 02:45.790
The, uh...

02:47.834 --> 02:48.668
For what?

02:48.751 --> 02:52.338
The things that you wear when it's
really bright outside and you wanna...

02:55.675 --> 02:57.635
My, uh-- What do you call 'em? The, uh...

02:57.719 --> 03:02.765
♪ And though I'm nobody's poet
I thought it wasn't half bad ♪

03:03.975 --> 03:07.520
[music slows down]
♪ Yes, I like Piña Coladas ♪

03:08.187 --> 03:09.022
[Belle] Kevin?

03:09.105 --> 03:10.940
♪ And gettin' caught in the rain ♪

03:11.024 --> 03:13.526
-I didn't mean to do it, I swear.
-Honey.

03:13.610 --> 03:15.069
-I'm sorry.
-[Belle] Kevin.

03:16.029 --> 03:16.863
[as Gilbert] Kevin.

03:17.906 --> 03:19.699
Kevin. Look at me, son.

03:22.493 --> 03:23.870
You made the right choice.

03:24.412 --> 03:26.873
You need to look forward, not back.

03:27.373 --> 03:29.500
You got the rest of your life
ahead of you.

03:30.126 --> 03:31.836
Now, this is what you're going to do.

03:32.712 --> 03:35.840
You're leaving here and driving
to the house where it happened.

03:35.924 --> 03:38.009
-I can't go back there, Mr. Gilbert.
-No, son.

03:38.092 --> 03:40.386
-Don't make me go back there.
-Son, there's no way

03:40.470 --> 03:42.430
you can think clearly right now. I can.

03:42.513 --> 03:45.141
That's what I'm offering you,
a clear path.

03:45.433 --> 03:46.601
You understand that?

03:48.978 --> 03:50.980
-Tell me, say the words.
-I do, Mr. Gilbert.

03:51.064 --> 03:53.900
-No, no, no. Say you understand.
-I--

03:54.567 --> 03:56.152
-I understand.
-Good.

03:57.111 --> 04:01.574
When you get to the house,
my guy will be there, okay?

04:01.658 --> 04:02.492
Okay.

04:02.575 --> 04:04.994
He'll need to know everything.
Every detail.

04:05.078 --> 04:08.581
He'll tell you what to do,
what you need to say.

04:09.874 --> 04:12.001
Any questions he asks,
you tell him the truth.

04:12.085 --> 04:13.461
The whole truth, son.

04:13.544 --> 04:16.631
You leave anything out,
you're only hurting yourself.

04:17.298 --> 04:18.132
Okay.

04:19.467 --> 04:20.969
Now get and move on. Come on.

04:22.679 --> 04:25.098
So, your guy, it's Luis, right?

04:25.181 --> 04:26.808
-From the boatyard?
-No.

04:31.145 --> 04:32.647
Well, how will I know who he is?

04:34.107 --> 04:36.109
He'll be the guy that isn't dead, Kevin.

04:48.871 --> 04:51.249
Oh, my God. Please don't throw up on me.

05:00.091 --> 05:01.968
[man] Luis, where you at, man?

05:03.553 --> 05:04.387
Luis.

05:05.972 --> 05:06.806
Shit.

05:07.932 --> 05:08.850
[gun cocks]

05:08.933 --> 05:09.767
Hey.

05:13.062 --> 05:15.273
Now, why does John Rayburn want me dead?

05:16.316 --> 05:17.150
Who?

05:18.735 --> 05:19.861
John Rayburn.

05:20.820 --> 05:23.031
-I never heard of him.
-Who the fuck...

05:23.489 --> 05:26.117
-do you work for, puto?
-I just drive. I don't know shit.

05:26.200 --> 05:28.494
Who... the...

05:29.078 --> 05:30.413
-fuck?
-Mr. Gilbert.

05:30.496 --> 05:32.582
Who the fuck is Mr. Gilbert?

05:32.665 --> 05:34.876
He's Roy Gilbert.
You don't fuck with this guy.

05:36.210 --> 05:38.838
I wanna fuck Roy Gilbert.

05:38.921 --> 05:39.756
And you.

05:46.262 --> 05:47.847
No, man. No, you...

05:49.223 --> 05:50.475
You didn't do nothing.

05:51.434 --> 05:52.810
You're just doing your job.

05:52.894 --> 05:54.979
You know, I'm gonna let you go, man.

05:55.063 --> 05:56.105
Thank you.

06:16.918 --> 06:17.794
[man] You'll be okay.

06:23.633 --> 06:25.593
As long as you do exactly what I tell you.

06:28.679 --> 06:30.306
I'm here to help you help yourself.

06:34.018 --> 06:36.187
You're gotta take the first step, okay?

06:45.655 --> 06:46.823
Come on inside.

07:11.347 --> 07:12.598
[girl chuckling]

07:31.659 --> 07:32.660
Where are you headed?

07:36.539 --> 07:37.540
North.

07:38.875 --> 07:40.042
North's good.

07:42.211 --> 07:43.421
Where are you coming from?

07:58.019 --> 07:59.145
[sighs]

08:02.023 --> 08:02.899
Two options.

08:03.983 --> 08:05.693
Either you were here, or you weren't.

08:06.652 --> 08:10.114
And if you weren't...
it'd be a whole lot easier.

08:11.491 --> 08:13.284
Great. Like, can we do that?

08:13.367 --> 08:16.162
Yeah, but you were here is the problem.

08:16.829 --> 08:18.664
All depends
on how much you can remember.

08:18.748 --> 08:20.791
Can't we just, like, wipe everything down?

08:20.875 --> 08:22.752
Clean the place really, really well?

08:23.336 --> 08:24.629
No, let's, um...

08:26.047 --> 08:27.840
Let's go back, step by step.

08:28.424 --> 08:30.218
What shoes are you wearing? Sneakers?

08:30.301 --> 08:32.386
-Mm, sandals.
-Socks?

08:32.470 --> 08:33.304
No.

08:34.055 --> 08:36.724
-Shorts, pants, t-shirt, tank--
-Shorts and a t-shirt.

08:36.807 --> 08:38.684
Is that his? Was he drinking?

08:41.604 --> 08:43.898
-It's not yours?
-No, no, I don't drink.

08:44.440 --> 08:45.399
Okay.

08:45.483 --> 08:47.652
So... you talk?

08:47.735 --> 08:50.363
Yeah. Well, it was more like an argument.
Um...

08:52.782 --> 08:55.785
I was trying to get him to stop doing
what he was about to do.

08:55.868 --> 08:57.578
-So, it was heated?
-Yeah.

08:57.662 --> 08:59.455
-You touch your face and all?
-What?

08:59.539 --> 09:02.333
Your face, did you touch it at all
during the argument?

09:02.416 --> 09:04.544
I don't know. Probably. Why?

09:04.627 --> 09:07.004
-Did you touch him?
-No, no. I never touched him.

09:07.755 --> 09:10.508
Good. But you're real worked up.

09:11.634 --> 09:12.927
Yeah, maybe.

09:14.136 --> 09:15.054
Is that good or bad?

09:16.097 --> 09:18.516
-Sweat's got your DNA.
-Fuck. Fuck.

09:18.599 --> 09:20.309
It's all right. Keep going.

09:24.397 --> 09:27.942
Um, so, yeah, we keep on arguing,
and then, uh...

09:31.529 --> 09:34.824
he comes up to my face really close,
and he says...

09:35.950 --> 09:37.493
some bullshit to me.

09:38.286 --> 09:40.413
And then, um, he threatens me.

09:40.955 --> 09:43.958
[sighs] And then he turns,
and he walks away.

09:44.041 --> 09:46.127
And that's when I-- That's when I--

09:46.669 --> 09:49.964
-I grabbed the thing.
-The what? From where?

09:50.047 --> 09:52.758
The-- On the table,
the fucking dolphin statue.

09:57.388 --> 09:58.514
And then, um...

10:01.892 --> 10:04.395
I swear, I just was trying
to make him stop, you know?

10:04.478 --> 10:06.022
I just wanted to get him to st--

10:06.105 --> 10:08.232
So, you hit him?

10:08.816 --> 10:09.650
I hit him.

10:12.820 --> 10:14.405
From behind? In the head?

10:15.781 --> 10:16.866
Just once.

10:17.700 --> 10:18.826
And then?

10:18.909 --> 10:20.828
And then he went down onto the ground.

10:20.911 --> 10:22.163
And then you hit him again?

10:22.705 --> 10:25.833
-Yeah, I guess.
-Three more times? Looks like three.

10:25.916 --> 10:26.876
Maybe it was three.

10:29.086 --> 10:31.047
[Kevin groans]

10:31.130 --> 10:32.798
Oh, Jesus. Fuck.

10:34.216 --> 10:36.427
I'm gonna be sick. Fuck.

10:37.136 --> 10:39.930
-[breathing heavily]
-It's okay, man. Stay with me, all right?

10:41.015 --> 10:43.768
Okay. So, then what happens?

10:44.226 --> 10:45.061
Um...

10:45.978 --> 10:46.854
Um...

10:46.937 --> 10:50.566
[grunts] Yeah, so, then I hit him,
and he goes down,

10:50.650 --> 10:53.694
and then I just dropped
the fucking statue.

10:54.987 --> 10:55.821
Okay, and then?

10:57.198 --> 10:58.991
I-I-I can't remember.

10:59.075 --> 10:59.909
Try.

11:00.493 --> 11:01.827
I was freaking out.

11:02.411 --> 11:04.163
So, did you sit down at all?

11:04.246 --> 11:06.499
No, I don't know. I can't--
I don't think so.

11:06.582 --> 11:08.751
Okay. Well, you must've done something.

11:12.838 --> 11:13.923
Yeah.

11:14.173 --> 11:15.257
Yeah, I did.

11:15.841 --> 11:16.675
What?

11:19.053 --> 11:20.012
Jesus.

11:20.721 --> 11:22.973
-You touch him? You try to help him?
-No.

11:24.558 --> 11:25.643
I pissed myself.

11:28.896 --> 11:29.730
Okay.

11:29.814 --> 11:33.067
-Um, where in the room exactly?
-I don't remember.

11:33.150 --> 11:34.443
I don't remember.

11:34.527 --> 11:37.822
Everything went black,
and then I just-- I left.

11:38.406 --> 11:40.199
Yeah, well, that settles that.

11:41.450 --> 11:43.119
-Piss.
-Why?

11:44.120 --> 11:46.038
I'm assuming you changed out
of the clothes you were wearing?

11:46.122 --> 11:47.456
Yes, obviously.

11:47.540 --> 11:49.375
Okay, so, then, piss in your pants now.

11:50.418 --> 11:51.419
Why?

11:51.502 --> 11:55.005
Look, you come in here, you're sweating,
you're jittery,

11:55.089 --> 11:57.842
-you got open-toed shoes, shorts, t-shirt.
-Okay, all right.

11:57.925 --> 12:01.053
Zero containment.
Then you touched the door, the dolphin,

12:01.637 --> 12:04.515
God knows what else,
then you piss all over the floor?

12:04.598 --> 12:06.600
I mean, the upshot?

12:06.976 --> 12:10.020
We're standing knee-deep in a swamp
of Kevin Rayburn.

12:10.771 --> 12:12.022
Then there's your DUI.

12:12.106 --> 12:14.733
-So, you're in the system. So, piss now.
-Okay, okay.

12:14.817 --> 12:16.193
I can't. I don't have to piss.

12:16.861 --> 12:18.696
-I'm, like, dehydrated.
-All right.

12:19.280 --> 12:20.114
Oh, boy.

12:28.539 --> 12:29.623
Drink that.

12:31.417 --> 12:33.252
Uh, where's the weapon?

12:35.337 --> 12:36.172
It's safe.

12:36.630 --> 12:38.799
The weapon is safe, man. I hid it.

12:39.133 --> 12:40.301
No one's gonna find that.

12:42.094 --> 12:43.596
-I need it.
-Why?

12:44.305 --> 12:47.808
Because nothing gets hidden. The surest
way to find something is to hide it.

12:47.892 --> 12:50.394
So, either I destroy it, or I plant it.

12:50.478 --> 12:51.854
What do you mean, "plant it"?

12:51.937 --> 12:54.064
One step at a time, okay?

12:54.148 --> 12:56.525
How long is it gonna take you
to get me the weapon?

12:56.609 --> 12:58.527
I don't know, 20 minutes. Maybe.

12:58.611 --> 12:59.945
So, half hour, tops?

13:00.488 --> 13:01.614
-Yeah, sure.
-All right.

13:01.697 --> 13:03.365
So, you'll be back in half an hour.

13:03.449 --> 13:04.533
[sighs]

13:04.617 --> 13:05.451
Um...

13:06.494 --> 13:07.786
Here, do me a favor.

13:08.996 --> 13:10.539
-I want your phone number.
-Why?

13:11.665 --> 13:13.501
-Just write it down.
-I'll just tell you.

13:17.213 --> 13:19.340
You need a reason for being here, okay?

13:19.423 --> 13:20.799
Marco called you to come over,

13:20.883 --> 13:23.969
so I'm gonna call you from that phone
in about 20 minutes.

13:24.512 --> 13:27.014
You pick it up,
you stay on for half a minute,

13:27.097 --> 13:29.517
and then there'll be a record
of you guys talking.

13:30.100 --> 13:31.310
What am I supposed to say?

13:31.685 --> 13:32.520
Nothing.

13:32.937 --> 13:36.482
It's just gonna be me on the other end,
so, you know, no one's gonna hear it.

13:36.565 --> 13:37.399
All right?

13:40.194 --> 13:42.655
Now let's go. Clock's ticking.
You go get that...

13:43.739 --> 13:44.823
you come right back...

13:46.200 --> 13:48.994
and by that time,
you should be ready to piss again.

13:57.461 --> 13:58.879
Wait, who's Eric?

13:59.797 --> 14:01.632
He's been calling and texting all night.

14:02.758 --> 14:05.761
Oh, that's right, that's right.
He called Marco when I was here.

14:06.262 --> 14:08.681
That's what made me snap.
That's Eric O'Bannon.

14:10.140 --> 14:11.517
Eric fucking O'Bannon.

14:17.565 --> 14:19.650
-What is wrong with you?
-Give me the money.

14:19.733 --> 14:21.235
No, get your own fucking cash.

14:21.318 --> 14:22.152
[Eric] Fuck.

14:22.695 --> 14:24.613
You piece of shit.
What did you do now, huh?

14:25.155 --> 14:29.201
I literally didn't do a fucking thing
and no one's gonna fucking believe me.

14:29.910 --> 14:31.871
-Then take the cash. Take it all.
-Got it.

14:31.954 --> 14:33.038
I have more.

14:34.540 --> 14:36.750
-Where?
-If I give you everything I have,

14:36.834 --> 14:39.169
you swear to me
I'll never see your face again?

14:39.753 --> 14:40.588
Look.

14:42.256 --> 14:44.049
Whatever they fucking tell you...

14:45.342 --> 14:46.927
don't believe a word. It's lies.

14:49.305 --> 14:50.848
Like it always fucking is.

14:53.601 --> 14:54.810
I didn't fucking kill him.

14:55.519 --> 14:57.313
Eric? Eric?

15:04.570 --> 15:05.779
[cell phone ringing]

15:07.197 --> 15:08.157
[grunts]

15:10.826 --> 15:11.660
Hello?

15:12.453 --> 15:13.871
-Yeah, right.
-[man over phone] Okay.

15:14.246 --> 15:15.998
-Thirty seconds, right?
-Right.

15:16.540 --> 15:18.292
Okay, what am I supposed to say?

15:18.375 --> 15:19.668
Stop panicking, all right?

15:19.752 --> 15:20.794
Okay, right. Okay.

15:20.878 --> 15:21.962
Hang on a bit longer.

15:25.215 --> 15:26.800
[panting]

15:30.638 --> 15:32.473
[Lou Reed's "Perfect Day" playing]

15:34.850 --> 15:35.684
Fuck.

15:35.768 --> 15:37.937
♪ Just a perfect day ♪

15:39.480 --> 15:42.942
♪ Feed animals in the zoo ♪

15:43.651 --> 15:44.526
[Kevin] It was John.

15:45.152 --> 15:45.986
[Marco] No shit.

15:46.654 --> 15:47.905
And you guys helped him.

15:49.865 --> 15:52.952
And the three of you...
[distorted] are going to fucking prison.

15:55.079 --> 15:56.538
[in normal voice]
So, do me a favor, all right?

15:56.872 --> 15:59.291
[distorted voice]
And get the fuck out of my house.

15:59.375 --> 16:00.626
[gasps]

16:01.669 --> 16:03.212
[tires screeching]

16:03.295 --> 16:04.630
[panting]

16:05.547 --> 16:06.590
[shouting]

16:07.466 --> 16:12.388
♪ You just keep me hanging on ♪

16:12.763 --> 16:14.098
No!

16:15.015 --> 16:16.934
[distorted voice]
You made the right choice.

16:17.017 --> 16:18.268
[Kevin] Fuck!

16:23.649 --> 16:24.525
Fuck!

16:25.150 --> 16:26.986
[breathing heavily]

16:30.197 --> 16:31.407
[shouting and sobbing]

16:33.367 --> 16:38.288
♪ You're going to reap just what you sow ♪

16:43.293 --> 16:44.920
[cell phone beeps, then dialing]

16:45.045 --> 16:46.588
Come on, John. Come on.

16:48.257 --> 16:51.135
You've reached John Rayburn.
Please leave a message.

16:56.098 --> 16:57.766
[cell phone beeps, then dialing]

16:59.184 --> 17:01.979
You've reached John Rayburn.
Please leave a message.

17:06.608 --> 17:07.443
Fuck.

17:13.073 --> 17:14.950
[cell phone beeps, then dialing]

17:15.075 --> 17:16.618
[cell phone buzzing]

17:16.910 --> 17:19.496
Doesn't seem like they're getting the hint
you're ignoring 'em.

17:31.508 --> 17:33.218
You need more fun in your life.

17:33.302 --> 17:34.136
Oh, yeah?

17:34.762 --> 17:37.014
[chuckles] Or not.

17:37.097 --> 17:38.348
But I'd say so.

17:39.933 --> 17:41.894
Were you always so serious?

17:42.561 --> 17:43.729
Even at my age?

17:46.440 --> 17:47.274
[John] Maybe.

17:48.859 --> 17:53.530
[chuckles] Dude, you gotta just...
hang out.

17:53.614 --> 17:55.365
You know, live your life.

17:55.699 --> 17:57.576
Go on and be a bad boy for once.

18:00.245 --> 18:01.622
[cell phone buzzing]

18:02.289 --> 18:03.290
That your wife?

18:04.416 --> 18:05.250
No.

18:06.335 --> 18:08.670
Got anyplace you really gotta be
right now?

18:09.713 --> 18:10.714
No.

18:11.590 --> 18:13.509
So, come party with us.

18:14.968 --> 18:16.136
Where are you going?

18:17.638 --> 18:19.056
Say yes, and I'll tell you.

18:20.599 --> 18:22.351
Trust me, you'll like it.

18:24.603 --> 18:25.687
[cell phone buzzing]

18:25.813 --> 18:28.148
You want me to answer it?
Tell him to quit calling?

18:32.653 --> 18:33.904
[John] No, it's my brother.

18:35.864 --> 18:37.616
-[girl] I got a baby brother.
-Yeah?

18:38.158 --> 18:38.992
Mm-hm.

18:39.576 --> 18:41.245
He's starting high school.

18:41.328 --> 18:43.497
Such a pain in the ass. Always...

18:44.540 --> 18:46.625
complaining and wanting attention.

18:46.708 --> 18:47.793
Fucking things up.

18:49.378 --> 18:50.796
[John] Fucking things up.

18:53.215 --> 18:54.383
[cell phone buzzing]

18:56.802 --> 18:58.720
-Hey, hey, baby bro.
-Look at me.

18:58.804 --> 19:00.514
-[Kevin] Oh, fuck.
-Give me that phone.

19:00.597 --> 19:03.642
-Where have you been? I've been calling.
-Give me the phone.

19:05.018 --> 19:06.228
You know what? I tried.

19:09.148 --> 19:11.441
-What the fuck do you want?
-Where have you been?

19:11.525 --> 19:14.486
-I've been calling you.
-I don't wanna talk to you, Kevin.

19:14.570 --> 19:16.613
Don't hang up, please.
Don't hang up, John.

19:16.697 --> 19:19.616
I have to tell you,
something really bad has happened, John.

19:19.700 --> 19:21.410
Some really, really, really bad shit.

19:21.910 --> 19:22.744
Oh, fuck.

19:24.079 --> 19:25.038
Oh, fuck, John.

19:26.373 --> 19:27.708
It's Marco, John.

19:28.625 --> 19:29.710
Marco's dead.

19:29.793 --> 19:30.878
[crying]

19:32.629 --> 19:33.964
He's dead, John.

19:34.673 --> 19:36.049
-Give me a minute.
-Oh, shit.

19:42.097 --> 19:42.931
Kevin.

19:43.056 --> 19:44.349
I don't know what happened.

19:45.684 --> 19:47.186
I went over to Marco's house.

19:47.895 --> 19:50.522
I didn't have an option. We got into it.

19:51.064 --> 19:52.232
And now he's--

19:52.691 --> 19:55.986
He's just laying there.
I don't think he's breathing.

19:56.069 --> 19:58.405
What the fuck do you mean
you didn't have a choice?

19:58.488 --> 20:02.326
Now Roy Gilbert's guy is waiting for me
over at Marco's, but I don't fucking know.

20:03.744 --> 20:06.288
Kevin, what the fuck
are you talking about, Gilbert?

20:06.371 --> 20:08.999
Roy Gilbert. He has this guy, okay?

20:09.625 --> 20:13.378
And he says that this guy says
that he can help me fix it.

20:13.462 --> 20:16.381
But I don't know, man.
This guy is fucking nuts.

20:16.465 --> 20:18.133
I think he's gonna fuck it up.

20:18.717 --> 20:19.885
Kevin, you listen to me.

20:20.719 --> 20:23.430
Listen to me. You stay
right where you are. Do you hear me?

20:23.513 --> 20:26.642
I don't want you to talk to anyone,
I don't want you to do anything,

20:26.725 --> 20:29.895
I don't want you to agree to anything,
you stay right where you are.

20:29.978 --> 20:32.022
-Okay, okay.
-Where are you, Kevin?

20:32.105 --> 20:33.732
Um... I'm, um...

20:34.483 --> 20:36.693
south of Mile Marker 80.
I had to pull over.

20:36.777 --> 20:38.862
-Stay there.
-Okay. I'm gonna wait right here.

20:38.946 --> 20:40.072
-You understand me?
-Where are you?

20:40.155 --> 20:41.531
It doesn't matter where I am!

20:41.615 --> 20:43.951
-You stay right there.
-Can I go home?

20:45.160 --> 20:46.203
Can you what?

20:46.286 --> 20:47.829
I gotta get a drink, man.

20:49.915 --> 20:51.375
I'm so thirsty, dude.

20:51.458 --> 20:53.377
Listen to me, you fucking asshole.

20:54.962 --> 20:56.505
You stay right where you are.

20:56.880 --> 20:58.590
Stay where you are, let me get there,

20:58.674 --> 21:01.009
and I promise
I'll do everything I can to help you.

21:01.093 --> 21:04.137
But don't you fucking leave where you are
right now, you hear me?

21:04.638 --> 21:05.514
Okay, great.

21:07.683 --> 21:08.684
I need you, John.

21:11.144 --> 21:12.271
[sighs]

21:12.521 --> 21:14.439
[whimpers]

21:20.529 --> 21:21.405
[chuckles]

21:35.502 --> 21:37.170
[cell phone dialing]

21:40.382 --> 21:42.050
Answer the fucking phone.

21:46.138 --> 21:46.972
John?

21:48.348 --> 21:50.267
-Who else knows?
-Where are you, man?

21:50.350 --> 21:52.936
Come on, just get here.
Please, please, please.

21:53.020 --> 21:55.480
-Meg?
-No. No, no. I didn't tell Meg.

21:55.564 --> 21:56.898
She doesn't know shit.

21:57.482 --> 21:58.734
Kevin, does Mom know?

22:00.235 --> 22:03.071
I didn't know what else to do.
I didn't have any other option.

22:03.155 --> 22:05.741
I was calling all night,
but you weren't picking up.

22:05.824 --> 22:08.952
So, don't you fucking blame me, all right?
I called you first.

22:09.536 --> 22:11.246
It's not my fucking fault, okay?

22:11.455 --> 22:14.750
This shit never would've happened, man,
it never would've happened...

22:16.043 --> 22:17.961
if you didn't do what you fucking did.

22:22.758 --> 22:23.592
John?

22:26.928 --> 22:27.763
John?

22:35.937 --> 22:36.772
John...

22:38.857 --> 22:39.691
[Belle] Hi there.

22:40.692 --> 22:41.651
Where you been?

22:44.613 --> 22:45.530
Where you been?

22:50.118 --> 22:51.286
[softly] John.

23:08.762 --> 23:09.930
[man] Detective Rayburn.

23:11.181 --> 23:12.349
Thank you for doing this.

23:12.557 --> 23:14.392
Just when you get a few days off, huh?

23:14.976 --> 23:15.936
Shit always happens.

23:16.144 --> 23:18.230
Take your eye off the ball
for a hot second...

23:19.022 --> 23:21.525
My wife had to go
to the emergency room last year, too.

23:22.025 --> 23:23.026
Middle of the night.

23:23.401 --> 23:24.611
Appendix burst.

23:26.029 --> 23:27.823
I'll get you home as fast as possible.

23:30.200 --> 23:31.034
Kevin.

23:32.494 --> 23:33.745
Where was it in the room?

23:36.665 --> 23:39.543
Um... On the table right there.

23:40.127 --> 23:40.961
Okay.

23:43.964 --> 23:45.966
So, listen, man. I talked to my brother.

23:46.675 --> 23:48.844
My brother John, he's a cop, and, uh...

23:49.594 --> 23:52.431
he doesn't want me to do anything
until he gets here, so...

23:54.099 --> 23:54.933
Okay.

23:56.309 --> 23:58.478
So, I think we should just really wait
for him.

23:59.354 --> 24:00.897
Okay, he knows you're here?

24:00.981 --> 24:01.815
Yeah.

24:02.649 --> 24:04.067
And when is that gonna be?

24:04.151 --> 24:05.152
-Not long.
-How long?

24:06.570 --> 24:07.571
-Soon.
-How soon?

24:08.572 --> 24:09.447
Um...

24:10.031 --> 24:10.866
Fuck.

24:11.533 --> 24:14.744
Fuck, I-- He doesn't know
that I'm "here" here.

24:14.828 --> 24:16.872
He thinks I'm at Mile Marker 80.

24:17.455 --> 24:19.624
It's where I called him from.
I gotta call him--

24:19.708 --> 24:21.918
-Kevin. Kevin.
-I gotta talk to my brother, man.

24:22.002 --> 24:23.211
-I don't--
-I know, I know.

24:23.295 --> 24:25.797
Listen, listen.
Let's just talk this through, okay?

24:25.881 --> 24:28.550
You came in, you saw somebody
standing over the body.

24:28.633 --> 24:30.969
Whoever that was killed Marco.

24:31.052 --> 24:33.471
They saw you, they got scared,
they ran. Who was it?

24:33.889 --> 24:35.056
I just-- I think--

24:35.515 --> 24:37.809
I think we should wait until he gets here.

24:37.893 --> 24:41.146
That's what we gotta come up with
so you can tell a convincing story.

24:41.229 --> 24:43.356
Forensics are top-notch these days.

24:43.607 --> 24:45.317
You know? It could be almost anybody.

24:45.609 --> 24:49.613
Used to be you had to have a story
that made sense. Now, we plant the DNA,

24:49.696 --> 24:51.531
they send it to the labs.

24:51.907 --> 24:53.825
Juries love science, okay?

24:53.909 --> 24:56.828
And the lawyers, they find a story
that matches the results.

24:57.412 --> 24:58.872
So, just pick somebody.

24:59.247 --> 25:00.248
I don't know.

25:01.333 --> 25:04.044
-Did he have a girlfriend?
-I don't know.

25:04.586 --> 25:05.712
Pissed-off ex?

25:06.713 --> 25:09.966
No, that's my sister. I don't think
she was pissed off at him, though.

25:10.050 --> 25:12.677
Well, it doesn't matter.
We can get her DNA. Easy enough.

25:12.761 --> 25:14.763
Are you...? No fucking way.

25:14.846 --> 25:17.015
You know, it's probably already
all around here.

25:17.098 --> 25:19.893
Fuck that. No way, man. That's my sister.
Come on, now.

25:20.852 --> 25:22.395
God damn it.

25:24.940 --> 25:25.774
Okay.

25:25.857 --> 25:27.234
[Kevin sighs]

25:27.317 --> 25:28.360
Well, who, then?

25:33.198 --> 25:34.282
What about Eric?

25:36.785 --> 25:37.786
It's good, right?

25:38.161 --> 25:40.789
He's been calling, texting.

25:43.541 --> 25:45.585
-He's already on Marco's phone.
-Yeah.

25:47.837 --> 25:48.755
All right.

25:49.339 --> 25:50.590
Now tell me what happened.

25:51.258 --> 25:52.634
Okay, so, um...

25:54.761 --> 25:55.804
So, I come in...

25:56.388 --> 25:57.722
and, uh, then I see him.

25:58.306 --> 25:59.724
-Who?
-Eric O'Bannon.

26:01.476 --> 26:02.352
And, uh...

26:03.728 --> 26:05.188
he's standing over the body.

26:05.272 --> 26:06.106
-Okay.
-Right?

26:06.189 --> 26:07.399
Standing here like this.

26:07.482 --> 26:08.316
Mm-hm.

26:09.067 --> 26:10.068
Yeah.

26:10.652 --> 26:13.822
And then I come in and he runs off.

26:14.864 --> 26:16.241
Yeah, it's not enough, though.

26:18.243 --> 26:19.077
So, what else?

26:19.452 --> 26:23.915
What if, um, you heard them arguing
as you approached the house?

26:23.999 --> 26:27.168
Okay, yeah. They're yelling at each other
when I got here. Right.

26:27.252 --> 26:30.964
Okay, that's good, but we gotta sell it
better. So, let's go back. Um...

26:31.798 --> 26:34.801
And by the way, Kevin,
this is all your choice, you know?

26:34.884 --> 26:37.846
If you weren't here,
I can try to make that work,

26:37.929 --> 26:39.764
but if you were here...

26:40.849 --> 26:42.350
I could turn you into a hero.

26:44.185 --> 26:45.020
Okay, yeah.

26:45.103 --> 26:47.147
Right? You tried to save Marco's life.

26:47.230 --> 26:48.064
Great.

26:48.148 --> 26:51.568
I mean, we got Marco's gun here.

26:51.651 --> 26:52.485
[Kevin] Right.

26:53.778 --> 26:54.738
[man] And, uh...

26:57.574 --> 26:59.618
-we got you standing there.
-Right.

27:00.702 --> 27:04.289
And then Eric sees you entering
the house, he raises the gun.

27:05.081 --> 27:06.416
Yeah, maybe...

27:08.752 --> 27:10.045
Oh, yeah. That's good, yeah.

27:10.128 --> 27:10.962
What?

27:11.046 --> 27:12.380
That'll sell it, man.

27:13.048 --> 27:15.008
Prove there was another person
in the room.

27:15.592 --> 27:17.969
How does him picking up the gun
prove he's here?

27:18.636 --> 27:19.846
Because he shot you.

27:20.430 --> 27:22.974
And then you call 911, and you report it.

27:23.058 --> 27:24.434
No fucking way.

27:24.976 --> 27:26.853
Stand still and let's finish this.

27:26.936 --> 27:29.105
We're gonna wait here
till my brother gets here.

27:29.189 --> 27:31.274
Listen, do not fucking shoot me.

27:44.412 --> 27:46.122
[woman] My gas.

27:46.206 --> 27:47.916
Jesus fucking Christ.

27:48.500 --> 27:49.709
Hi, Mom. [cracks knuckles]

27:50.293 --> 27:52.128
-My gas.
-What?

27:52.712 --> 27:53.546
It's--

27:53.838 --> 27:54.714
You got gas?

27:54.798 --> 27:56.132
My gas.

27:56.674 --> 27:58.426
Your gas is out. Okay.

27:58.843 --> 28:00.720
We got a tank. We got a spare tank.

28:00.804 --> 28:01.971
Empty.

28:02.555 --> 28:05.141
It's empty? Why the fuck is it empty, Ma?

28:06.017 --> 28:07.560
Chelsea's supposed
to bring you fresh ones.

28:07.644 --> 28:09.145
It's not supposed to be empty.

28:10.230 --> 28:12.899
Where am I supposed to get one
in the middle of the night?

28:13.483 --> 28:14.442
Hospital.

28:15.360 --> 28:16.903
Okay. Call Chelsea.

28:16.986 --> 28:18.780
She isn't picking up.

28:19.197 --> 28:20.615
You need to go.

28:21.116 --> 28:22.534
-Hospital.
-Ma, I...

28:24.035 --> 28:27.497
I love you. I can't fucking deal
with this right now, okay?

28:27.580 --> 28:30.625
You gotta hold this thing
in your nose, put your hand up there.

28:30.708 --> 28:33.628
It'll be okay, okay?
This is not my fault, okay?

28:33.711 --> 28:36.965
You're gonna keep calling Chelsea.
It's gonna be good, okay?

28:37.632 --> 28:39.217
Just keep calling her, okay?

28:42.387 --> 28:44.097
You little cunt.

28:54.524 --> 28:55.567
I heard that, Mom.

29:01.740 --> 29:03.158
[indistinct radio chatter]

29:32.020 --> 29:33.188
[groans]

29:52.624 --> 29:54.000
[phone dialing]

29:55.460 --> 29:57.295
Come on, answer, you fucking fuckwad.

29:58.087 --> 29:58.922
[line beeps]

29:59.005 --> 30:01.800
Ozzy, I got your fucking payday
for you, dude.

30:01.883 --> 30:03.510
I got John Rayburn served up to you

30:03.593 --> 30:06.304
like a pig
on a fucking silver fucking stick.

30:06.763 --> 30:08.973
He's done some seriously bad fucking shit,

30:09.057 --> 30:11.392
and he's not gonna get away with it
if we act fast.

30:11.476 --> 30:12.977
So, you gotta fucking call me.

30:13.561 --> 30:14.479
So, fucking call me.

30:16.022 --> 30:17.607
[dance music playing over speakers]

30:23.738 --> 30:24.739
Hey, that, um--?

30:25.156 --> 30:26.741
That polar freeze?

30:27.325 --> 30:29.494
Is that the one
that turns your tongue all blue?

30:30.119 --> 30:31.621
Wha...

30:31.704 --> 30:32.539
What was that?

30:34.499 --> 30:35.333
Yeah, probably.

30:39.254 --> 30:41.422
Okay, good. I'll have one.

30:42.173 --> 30:43.007
What size?

30:44.926 --> 30:45.760
Um...

30:46.845 --> 30:47.679
large.

30:55.895 --> 30:57.230
-Okay, Kevin--
-You know what?

30:57.313 --> 30:59.899
Fuck this, man. This is crazy, okay?

30:59.983 --> 31:00.900
I'm done here.

31:00.984 --> 31:04.529
I'm gonna go back home, get John,
then we'll come back here. You got it?

31:04.612 --> 31:08.616
Kevin, if you move, I can't guarantee
where the bullet will strike.

31:09.075 --> 31:10.201
So, just stand still.

31:10.285 --> 31:12.412
All right? Don't move.

31:12.871 --> 31:14.747
-Fuck you. I'm out of here.
-Don't move.

31:18.084 --> 31:19.711
Fuck. Shit.

31:20.253 --> 31:21.963
-Ow.
-Fuck.

31:22.046 --> 31:23.673
I told you to stand still.

31:24.090 --> 31:27.427
You-- You fucking shot me, you bitch!

31:27.510 --> 31:28.803
You fucking shot me!

31:28.887 --> 31:29.971
No, I didn't.

31:30.054 --> 31:31.598
Listen to me. Listen to me, okay?

31:31.681 --> 31:34.726
We don't have a lot of time.
I didn't shoot you. You understand?

31:35.310 --> 31:37.770
-Get an ambulance.
-Eric O'Bannon shot you

31:37.854 --> 31:40.607
after you heard yelling,
after you surprised him

31:40.690 --> 31:42.734
and saw that he killed Detective Diaz.

31:42.817 --> 31:44.027
What the fuck, man?

31:44.110 --> 31:45.278
Okay, Kevin?

31:45.361 --> 31:48.031
Listen, man.
Kevin, Kevin, stay with me, okay?

31:48.114 --> 31:51.034
I need you to call 911 and report this.
Where's your phone?

31:51.117 --> 31:52.285
I can't. I can't.

31:52.368 --> 31:53.578
Okay, all right.

31:53.661 --> 31:55.622
-I don't feel my legs.
-Stay, stay with me.

31:55.705 --> 31:56.664
Okay, now, listen.

31:56.748 --> 32:00.627
I need you to dial and call 911 now.

32:01.669 --> 32:04.088
-I don't feel--
-I'm not fucking around, Kevin, okay?

32:04.172 --> 32:07.717
I need you to dial 911 now, okay?

32:08.593 --> 32:09.677
[man sighs]

32:10.595 --> 32:11.471
Oh, fuck.

32:13.806 --> 32:15.141
[keypad beeping, then dialing]

32:25.068 --> 32:26.653
911. What's your emergency?

32:27.487 --> 32:29.322
-Answer her.
-911. What's your emergency?

32:29.405 --> 32:32.742
-Answer her. Tell her where you are.
-If you need the police, press one.

32:33.493 --> 32:35.870
If you need the fire department,
press two.

32:36.454 --> 32:38.498
If you need an ambulance, press three.

32:39.749 --> 32:42.627
Is there someone there with you
who can give me an address?

32:45.755 --> 32:46.923
I just heard shots fired.

32:48.383 --> 32:49.425
Hello?

32:49.509 --> 32:51.678
If you can hear me, just stay on the line.

33:08.611 --> 33:10.321
[cell phone dialing]

33:14.033 --> 33:16.119
[woman over phone]
911. What's your emergency?

33:16.202 --> 33:18.705
[man] I just heard shots.
A few shots at my neighbor's house.

33:19.205 --> 33:20.748
Can you give me the address, sir?

33:20.832 --> 33:23.001
It's a cop's house. Diaz. Marco Diaz.

33:25.086 --> 33:27.005
The police department is on the way, sir.

33:27.088 --> 33:30.591
Stay in your house and lock your doors
and windows. They'll be there soon.

33:36.264 --> 33:37.682
[police sirens wailing]

34:26.773 --> 34:28.441
We got a male vic, he's clear.

34:29.025 --> 34:29.984
Come on, let's move.

34:31.652 --> 34:32.695
We got a faint pulse.

34:36.908 --> 34:38.076
[man 1] Bullet's still lodged.

34:39.077 --> 34:40.828
Sir? Sir, can you hear me?

34:41.329 --> 34:42.497
Please respond to me.

34:43.206 --> 34:44.624
[cell phone ringing]

34:49.003 --> 34:49.837
Rayburn.

34:58.096 --> 34:59.388
What was that address again?

35:02.308 --> 35:03.351
[man] How's the BP?

35:04.060 --> 35:05.144
[woman] It's dropping fast.

35:05.228 --> 35:06.312
[EKG beeping]

35:07.021 --> 35:08.231
[man] Push more fluids.

35:10.191 --> 35:11.651
[woman] We gotta stop the bleeding...

35:14.153 --> 35:16.864
-Keep pressure on the arm.
-[man] Pulse ox is fading.

35:16.948 --> 35:18.074
[EKG beeping rapidly]

35:20.118 --> 35:21.160
[John] Take a left up here.

35:30.545 --> 35:31.879
[rock music playing over speakers]

35:33.047 --> 35:35.007
Oh, what the fuck? Fuck.

35:58.656 --> 35:59.740
[Carol] John.

36:00.366 --> 36:03.703
One victim deceased, Detective Diaz,
and one shot is your brother.

36:06.164 --> 36:08.332
What the fuck are you talking about,
my brother?

36:09.083 --> 36:11.335
-You didn't know?
-No. Dispatch said that Marco--

36:11.711 --> 36:14.338
-The fuck are you talking about?
-Jesus, John. I'm sorry.

36:15.631 --> 36:16.465
Marco sho--

36:18.676 --> 36:19.844
Looks like he was beaten.

36:21.929 --> 36:24.182
Blunt force head trauma.
It's a fucking mess.

36:26.767 --> 36:28.561
Kevin is on his way to Island Village.

36:28.644 --> 36:31.272
He took two rounds.
One in the leg, one in the stomach.

36:39.614 --> 36:40.781
Did he say anything?

36:40.865 --> 36:42.033
No. No, no.

36:42.742 --> 36:44.994
He was unconscious when the unis arrived.

36:45.077 --> 36:47.330
John, go be with your brother.

36:47.747 --> 36:49.290
We'll handle things here.

36:49.999 --> 36:51.042
I ju-- I...

36:53.294 --> 36:54.754
-Suspects?
-[Carol] None.

36:55.713 --> 36:57.256
We gotta start working the scene.

37:00.635 --> 37:01.469
[softly] Kevin.

37:07.850 --> 37:08.976
Hey, hey, hey.

37:10.561 --> 37:11.896
We're in this together, John.

37:13.314 --> 37:14.607
We'll get the motherfucker.

37:47.098 --> 37:48.599
[inhales]

38:03.155 --> 38:03.990
Fuck.

38:06.742 --> 38:07.743
[Kevin] It's Marco, John.

38:08.995 --> 38:09.870
Marco's dead.

38:12.832 --> 38:18.796
I didn't have an option. We got into it,
and now he's just laying there.

38:19.338 --> 38:22.174
And now, Roy Gilbert's guy is waiting
for me over at Marco's,

38:22.258 --> 38:23.801
but I don't fucking know.

38:24.969 --> 38:26.929
[John] Kevin, what the fuck
are you talking about?

38:27.013 --> 38:28.431
[Kevin] Gilbert. Roy Gilbert.

38:32.018 --> 38:34.937
[John] Listen to me. You stay
right where you are. You hear me?

38:35.021 --> 38:37.231
I don't want you to talk to anyone,
I don't want you to do anything,

38:37.315 --> 38:41.068
I don't want you to agree to anything,
you stay right where you are.

38:42.028 --> 38:44.030
[Kevin] It's not my fucking fault, okay?

38:44.113 --> 38:46.032
This shit never would've happened, man,

38:46.115 --> 38:49.660
it never would've happened
if you didn't do what you fucking did.

39:00.421 --> 39:01.922
[chattering]

39:11.182 --> 39:12.224
Hey, um...

39:12.975 --> 39:15.978
Neighbor over there is the one
that called after hearing shots.

39:16.937 --> 39:20.066
Your brother called 911,
but he was unable to give an address.

39:20.274 --> 39:21.609
Neighbor didn't see anything.

39:22.234 --> 39:23.861
We're going door to door right now.

39:23.944 --> 39:25.654
Yeah. I already set up a perimeter.

39:26.405 --> 39:29.367
Any other angles?
Cases you guys were working on together?

39:29.867 --> 39:30.701
No.

39:31.911 --> 39:33.621
[Carol] Anyone getting out of prison?
Guys--

39:33.704 --> 39:35.039
Fuck, Carol, I don't know.

39:35.581 --> 39:37.708
[Aguirre] I gotta say it
'cause I'm thinking it, okay?

39:39.335 --> 39:40.669
Diana and the kids okay?

39:41.545 --> 39:42.380
They're safe?

39:45.216 --> 39:47.134
Yeah, they're at home in bed asleep. Why?

39:47.259 --> 39:48.844
I already dispatched a patrol.

39:49.845 --> 39:52.223
'Cause whoever did this
could be targeting you, too.

39:57.561 --> 39:58.396
Thank you.

40:00.356 --> 40:02.066
His, uh, next of kin?

40:04.485 --> 40:05.528
I'll do it.

40:05.611 --> 40:06.737
[cell phone buzzing]

40:08.364 --> 40:09.198
Excuse me.

40:12.076 --> 40:13.619
[Carol] Anything else I can do for you?

40:15.746 --> 40:16.747
I need your car.

40:18.916 --> 40:21.460
Sure. Keys are in it.

40:26.132 --> 40:27.007
Got anything?

40:27.091 --> 40:30.719
[man] Yeah. I got the, uh, time of death
between 60 and 90 minutes ago.

40:32.388 --> 40:33.597
Hey, John.

40:35.558 --> 40:38.102
I'm sorry about your baby brother.
I hope he's okay.

40:49.321 --> 40:50.656
[phone dialing]

40:55.661 --> 40:57.329
-[woman over phone] Hello?
-Knock, knock.

40:57.872 --> 40:59.165
I'm not in the mood.

40:59.248 --> 41:00.541
Oh, come on.

41:01.041 --> 41:03.836
-Who's there?
-Ozzy, what do you need?

41:04.253 --> 41:05.713
Well, for starters...

41:06.505 --> 41:07.381
[sniffs]

41:07.465 --> 41:09.842
I need a goddamn shower.
That's for damn sure.

41:11.552 --> 41:13.512
-Still in Miami, right?
-Yeah.

41:14.972 --> 41:16.348
-I'll see you soon.
-All right.

41:21.896 --> 41:22.771
[knocking on door]

41:26.484 --> 41:27.359
[knocking on door]

41:31.822 --> 41:32.698
[knocking on door]

41:53.302 --> 41:54.386
Is John okay?

41:57.014 --> 41:58.641
[woman]
The doctor will be right with you.

42:00.100 --> 42:03.437
Excuse me, I was promised an update
from Dr. Vasson.

42:03.521 --> 42:05.064
Could you please contact him?

42:05.147 --> 42:06.023
He's in surgery.

42:06.732 --> 42:07.816
[Diana] Belle.

42:09.193 --> 42:11.237
Oh, my God. I'm so sorry.

42:11.320 --> 42:12.154
[crying]

42:12.238 --> 42:13.113
Kev--

42:13.197 --> 42:16.033
John sent an officer to get me.
What's the status on Kevin?

42:16.116 --> 42:18.869
They won't tell me. They--
No one's telling me anything.

42:18.953 --> 42:22.498
He's in surgery,
and they said that he was at Marco's.

42:22.581 --> 42:24.083
-He's what?
-I don't know.

42:25.668 --> 42:26.961
I don't know. He...

42:28.087 --> 42:30.005
Where's Meg? Has anyone seen her or John?

42:30.089 --> 42:31.549
-I don't know.
-Okay.

42:31.632 --> 42:32.675
-Okay, I got it.
-[John] Hi.

42:37.012 --> 42:38.097
Is he out of surgery yet?

42:38.180 --> 42:40.224
-They won't tell me anything.
-[woman] Belle Rayburn?

42:41.934 --> 42:45.563
Dr. Vasson wanted to tell you your husband
made it through his first surgery.

42:45.646 --> 42:48.107
They've stopped the bleeding
from one of the wounds,

42:48.190 --> 42:50.317
and they're working on the second one now.

42:50.985 --> 42:55.072
It'd be helpful to know if any of you have
Kevin's blood type to donate just in case.

42:56.574 --> 42:59.410
I think Meg does.
But he should really be in Miami.

42:59.493 --> 43:02.246
When he gets out of surgery,
give me a call, I'll come back.

43:02.329 --> 43:04.665
-Miami Baptist has the best doctor--
-Who did this?

43:04.748 --> 43:07.209
-I don't know.
-You find out who did this.

43:07.293 --> 43:10.004
-Could you have him transferred to Miami?
-Yes, yes.

43:10.087 --> 43:12.673
-That's exactly what I'm gonna try to do.
-[Belle] You find out.

43:13.257 --> 43:14.425
Oh, my God.

43:24.393 --> 43:25.728
[car alarm wailing nearby]

43:55.341 --> 43:56.884
[woman on recording]
Please record your voice message.

43:56.967 --> 43:58.469
-[beeps]
-[Sally] Whatever you did...

43:59.511 --> 44:02.514
whatever happened, you better pray
my son is gonna be all right.

44:02.598 --> 44:04.767
And fucking call me back, Roy.

44:16.862 --> 44:17.696
Hey.

44:23.702 --> 44:24.536
Meg.

44:29.083 --> 44:29.917
[Meg] John?

44:33.837 --> 44:35.172
John, is that you?

44:36.423 --> 44:37.257
Yeah.

44:40.719 --> 44:44.598
Have you seen Kevin?
I called you a million times.

44:47.768 --> 44:50.396
You need to come with me to the hospital
and give blood.

44:51.146 --> 44:52.231
Kevin's been shot.

44:54.483 --> 44:55.317
You hear me?

44:56.693 --> 45:00.197
[Meg] Kevin is at Marco's, you know?

45:00.781 --> 45:03.617
I gotta go to work in the morning, okay?

45:04.993 --> 45:06.203
[Meg groans]

45:25.597 --> 45:27.558
[doorbell rings]

45:31.979 --> 45:33.981
Aren't you a sight for sore eyes?

45:37.234 --> 45:38.485
Holy shit.

45:39.653 --> 45:41.613
Yeah, well, you should see the other guys.

45:43.991 --> 45:45.742
Don't fucking sit on my couch.

45:47.578 --> 45:48.954
No, I don't need a doctor.

45:49.621 --> 45:52.666
I have no idea where Roy Gilbert is.
He's not answering my calls.

45:52.749 --> 45:56.628
I only have his cell phone number.
You don't have any other contact for him?

45:56.712 --> 45:59.006
I called his home.
He's probably long gone by now,

45:59.089 --> 46:01.341
on his boat or his plane,
or however he does it.

46:02.092 --> 46:04.178
Vanishing is his best talent.

46:04.970 --> 46:07.222
Where's Meg?
She's not answering my calls either.

46:07.306 --> 46:10.142
-God, she's useless.
-If you're dizzy, why don't you sit down?

46:11.393 --> 46:13.645
Place your head
between your knees and sit down.

46:13.729 --> 46:16.565
Would you just stop ordering me around?

46:17.149 --> 46:17.983
I just need water.

46:18.066 --> 46:21.153
You want me to get you a glass of water,
I'll get you water.

46:21.236 --> 46:22.529
[sighs]

46:30.537 --> 46:32.748
If you have tightness in your chest...

46:34.082 --> 46:35.417
we need to call the doctor.

46:46.803 --> 46:47.971
I know everything, John.

46:51.350 --> 46:52.518
Meg told me all of it.

46:55.103 --> 46:58.482
And I don't wanna hear you making excuses
for why you did what you did.

46:58.565 --> 47:00.317
I don't want you apologizing to me,

47:00.400 --> 47:02.819
or asking me to forgive you
for anything you've done.

47:02.903 --> 47:06.281
I just want you to do one thing...
and one thing only.

47:06.365 --> 47:09.076
I want you to find who shot your brother.

47:28.136 --> 47:30.556
When you went to Roy Gilbert,
what did he say to you?

47:31.557 --> 47:32.641
He said, uh...

47:34.476 --> 47:36.562
he had a guy who could help Kevin.

47:38.897 --> 47:40.941
They'd work together and, uh...

47:42.526 --> 47:45.529
figure out who... else to blame.

47:46.822 --> 47:49.825
What else did he say about the guy?
Did he mention anything else?

47:50.409 --> 47:52.869
No, he said the less I knew the better.

47:52.953 --> 47:56.290
But he'd get Kevin out from under this.

47:58.417 --> 47:59.751
To frame someone else.

48:00.294 --> 48:01.169
Oh.

48:01.712 --> 48:03.046
That's the word.

48:03.130 --> 48:03.964
Frame.

48:04.047 --> 48:05.048
[chuckles]

48:08.260 --> 48:09.094
Mom, I--

48:09.177 --> 48:10.137
[cell phone ringing]

48:21.273 --> 48:22.107
It's Belle.

48:25.319 --> 48:26.153
[sighs]

48:33.910 --> 48:34.911
[cell phone vibrates]

49:01.980 --> 49:03.273
[EKG beeping]

49:05.233 --> 49:06.068
Kevin.

49:08.820 --> 49:09.655
Kevin.

49:11.865 --> 49:12.699
Can you hear me?

49:17.162 --> 49:19.748
There are gonna be a lot of questions
coming at you.

49:22.501 --> 49:24.419
And you're gonna say, "I don't remember."

49:26.713 --> 49:27.756
Do you understand that?

49:28.173 --> 49:29.883
You're gonna say, "I don't remember."

49:35.347 --> 49:38.600
You're gonna give me a chance
to try to figure something out for you.

49:40.185 --> 49:41.395
[knocking on door]

49:56.576 --> 49:57.411
How's he doing?

50:02.374 --> 50:03.250
In and out.

50:05.377 --> 50:06.211
Well...

50:06.795 --> 50:08.296
the surgeon said he's a fighter.

50:09.005 --> 50:10.132
[scoffs]

50:10.257 --> 50:11.091
Yeah.

50:11.925 --> 50:15.095
The doc also said when Kevin
was coming out of anesthesia...

50:16.179 --> 50:17.305
he ID'd the shooter.

50:19.558 --> 50:20.392
Eric O'Bannon.

50:22.269 --> 50:23.520
Eric O'Bannon?

50:23.603 --> 50:24.438
Yeah.

50:28.775 --> 50:30.610
We're ready for you, Detective Rayburn.

50:31.778 --> 50:33.155
Go ahead. We'll talk later.

50:35.449 --> 50:36.366
Yeah.

51:15.947 --> 51:17.783
You're stronger than you think.

51:22.037 --> 51:24.956
You're stronger than your family thinks.

51:32.214 --> 51:33.548
We're gonna get through this.

51:37.219 --> 51:38.678
And we're gonna have our baby.

51:43.016 --> 51:44.226
And we're gonna love him.

51:46.144 --> 51:47.604
And we're gonna keep him safe.

51:53.151 --> 51:54.986
And you're gonna watch him grow up.

52:03.620 --> 52:04.496
I love you.

52:14.965 --> 52:15.799
I love you.

